<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.257527>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Trianguloscalpellum pentacrinarum (Pilsbry, 1907). Holotype: a—right lateral view, b—left lateral view, cpeduncule attached to a cirrus of Neocrinus decorus (Thomson, 1864). Scale bar 5 mm. L 2 = lower latus, inframedian latus or second latus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/257527/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.257528>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Trianguloscalpellum pentacrinarum (Pilsbry, 1907). Supplementary material, NHM UK 1884.6. 20.5, dissected to reveal the inside surface of plates: a—right lateral view, b—left lateral view, c—rostral view, d—carinal view. Zevinaella volentis gen. et sp. nov. Holotype: e—the inside surface of the capitulum, soft body parts removed. Scale bar 5 mm. R = rostrum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/257528/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

